 the same year Hannah died, and Sarah Beaumont in 1837 the same year Thankful died. He moved his family across an extraordinary geographic arc: Northampton Massachusetts to Conway Massachusetts, then Derby Vermont, then thirteen years in Montreal Canada from 1815 to 1828, then Sunderland Massachusetts, finally Champlain New York where he died in 1844 at age seventy-four."},{"number":2,"category":"death","header":"Memorialized with all three wives in Montreal","body":"Elisha Lyman Jr. died at Champlain New York February 21, 1844 at age seventy-four. He was buried at Cimetière Mont-Royal in Montreal — the city where his second wife Thankful had died in 1837, and where his sons William, Benjamin, and Henry had settled to build the Lyman Brothers drug empire. A family memorial at Mount Royal commemorates Elisha together with all three of his wives."}],"slug":"elisha-lyman-jr-1770"},"H00463":{"id":"H00463","has_descendants_documented":true,"classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":true,"generation_from_thomas":6,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"birth":{"year":1768,"month":5,"day":16,"city":"Windsor","state":"Connecticut"},"death":{"year":1814,"month":2,"day":25,"city":"Derby","state":"Vermont"},"burial":{"cemetery_id":"CEM327","plot_notes":"Derby Center Cemetery, Orleans County Vermont — per FindAGrave #235170328. Died a year before husband Elisha relocated the surviving family to Montreal."},"parents":{"father_id":"H00241","mother_id":"I00160"},"marriages":[{"children_ids":["HD0580","HD4172","HD4173","HD0581","HD4174","HD4175","HD4176","HD4177","HD0582","HD0583"],"spouse_id":"X01250","marriage_number":1}],"tags":["not_yet_fully_entered","canada_migration"],"sources":[{"short":"Edward Hooker 1909","page":"Entry 463"}],"gender":"female","number_of_marriages":1,"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"cross_connections":[],"bio":{"display_name":"Hannah Stiles Lyman","first_name":"Hannah","last_name":"Lyman","married_names":["Lyman"],"maiden_name":"Stiles"},"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[{"bib_id":"BIB008"}],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"death","header":"Died at forty-five, before family's Montreal move","body":"Hannah Stiles Lyman died February 25, 1814 at Derby Vermont, age forty-five — one year before her widower Elisha relocated the surviving family to Montreal where they would remain for thirteen years. She had borne ten children over twenty years; two had died in infancy (Ashbel Stiles in 1796 and Horace in 1798) and the youngest, Henry, was only four months old when she died. Her three eldest surviving sons would become the founders of Lyman Brothers, the largest pharmaceutical wholesaler in Canada."},{"number":2,"category":"family","header":"Mother of the Lyman drug dynasty","body":"Three of Hannah Stiles Lyman's sons — William (Montreal druggist), Benjamin (co-founder of Lyman Brothers, the largest pharmaceutical company in Canada), and Henry (Montreal lawyer and Lyman Brothers partner) — together built the Lyman drug empire across Montreal and Toronto. Her grandson Henry Herbert Lyman would later bequeath his entomology collection to McGill University, founding what became the Lyman Entomological Museum."}],"slug":"hannah-lyman-1768"}},"burialCemetery":{"id":"CEM328","name":"Cimetière Mont-Royal","city":"Outremont","state":"Montréal Region","country":"Canada","founded":1852,"wikipedia_url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mount_Royal_Cemetery","primary_url":"https://www.findagrave.com/cemetery/639448/cimeti%C3%A8re-mont-royal","hooker_connections":["HD0580","HD0583","HD0584","HD0585","HD0586","HD0587","HD0588","HD4178","HD4182","HD4183","HD4187","HD4188","HD4189","HD4190","HD4191","HD4192","HD4194","HD4196","HD4198","HD4199","HD4210","HD4211","HD4213","HD4214","HD4219","HD4220","HD4221","HD4228","HD4229","I00630","I00631","I00632","I00634","I00640","I00641","I00643","I00645","I00646","I00647","X01250","X01251","X01252","X01253","X01591","X02825","I01230"],"notes":"Cimetière Mont-Royal (Mount Royal Cemetery), Outremont, Montreal QC. Major Protestant cemetery founded 1852 on the slopes of Mount Royal. Burial site of multiple members of the Lyman family — Hannah Stiles Lyman's descendants who became prominent Montreal druggists, lawyers, and civic figures: Elisha Lyman Jr. (with his three wives memorialized together), Henry Lyman, Mary Corse Lyman, Henry Herbert Lyman (later commemorated here after death on the Empress of Ireland 1914), Albert Clarence Lyman, Frederick Stiles Lyman, Edith Mary Louise Lyman, and others."},"institutionsById":{},"crossConnections":[]}